====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# One who [[clap]]s; a person who [[applaud]]s by clapping the hands.
# {{senseid|en|bell}} An object so suspended inside a [[bell]] that it may hit the bell and cause it to ring; a [[clanger]] or [[tongue]].
# A wooden mechanical device used as a [[scarecrow]]; bird-scaring [[rattle]], a wind-rattle or a wind-clapper.
#* '''1896''', Sabine Baring-Gould, ''Arminell, a social romance'', [[Wikisource:Arminell, a social romance/Chapter 37|Ch.&nbsp;37]]:
#*: "Sir, sir! folks' tongues go like the '''clappers''' in the fields to drive away the blackbirds. A very little wind makes 'em rattle wonderfully."
# A [[clapstick]] {{q|musical instrument}}.
# {{lb|en|sewing}} A [[pounding block]].
# The [[chattering damsel]] of a [[mill]].
#{{lb|en|ice hockey}} A [[slapshot]]
# {{lb|en|cinematography}} The hinged part of a [[clapperboard]], used to synchronise images and soundtrack, or the clapperboard itself.

